entries.femaleVariant: Ugh, Mike, we're talkin' about the cornerstone of my platform. I'm not doing a U-turn just 'cause Night Corp--
Look, I gotta go. Make the amendments, we'll pow-wow later.
It's good to see you again.
He's just about done prepping for the debate.
I've rescheduled all his meetings out of the office today. The office meaning here, so – nobody'll bother us.
No, I'm not sucking anyone's dick just so they can fuck me in the ass!
V? We're upstairs.
Thanks.
Something happen?
Come on, Jeff'll explain everything.
V – glad you could make it.
Grab a seat, please. I'll explain why I asked you to come over.
Notify the cops yet?
Why me?
Why me of all people? Wouldn't rather have a detective look into it?
entries.maleVariant: Why me of all people? Wouldn't you rather have a detective look into it?

entries.femaleVariant: Prefer to use tried-and-tested contacts.
Former mayor's death – you unraveled that mystery.
Notify the badges yet?
We don't want any buzz around this, no attention whatever.
You know... NCPD's full of people who like the occasional stray eddie.
If we reported a break-in, the media'd descend on us like a swarm of locusts.
No badges – gotcha.
So, unusual how?
A couple of days back, dead of night, something wakes me, a noise. I grab my pistol and come out of the bedroom.
See a stranger. He looks like he's about to reach for it, so I pull the trigger.
Nail him?
No idea – my head started spinning and I passed out. No trace of him the morning after.
SSI have anything to say?
Describe the intruder for me?
Anything missing from the apartment?
What did the intruder look like?
I can't remember much – it was dark. He was wearing some sort of mask...
Or was it an implant? Ehh, couldn't really get a good look at 'im.
Security look into this, say anything?
This is where things get a little weird.
They claim there's no sign of a break-in or of a shot being fired.
Security cams didn't record anything. Guard outside didn't see or hear anything…
They suggested Jeff just must've had a bad dream.
Convenient answer…
Liz gave security the day off so I could call you in.
Intruder take anything? Break anything?
entries.maleVariant: Intruder take anything? Uh, break anything?

entries.femaleVariant: Nothing missing…
I haven't noticed any damage, either. Jeff must've scared him off before he could do anything.
Elizabeth didn't see him, either?
I slept through the whole thing. Election season takes its toll on you...
Could be, could also be somebody behind SSI.
Doubt it.
This security outfit, SSI... who are they?
entries.maleVariant: This um, security outfit, SSI... who are they?

entries.femaleVariant: Been on the market the last fifteen years... They have clients across the city.
If memory serves, they came recommended... an acquaintance.
Weldon Holt? He's my main rival. Fighting for the same seat at the table.
Holt's poll numbers have been dropping…
Need to have a look around.
Anything else I should know?
Wouldn't mind taking a look around the apartment.
Of course. Liz can give you the tour. Gotta run to a meeting. Soon as you learn anything, let me know.
Wh-bother us at doing what, exactly?
entries.maleVariant: Um, bother us at doing what, exactly?

entries.femaleVariant: You'll know in a minute.
Can't blame ya.
Jefferson.
[Sit]
Of course, we notified SSI about the incident – our private security.
Said you passed out?
When did you come to?
That's right, just after I fired.
What then?
Nothing. I woke up in bed the next morning. Killer headache, to boot.
Any idea how you made it back to your bed?
Nope... none. Elizabeth's at a loss, too.
You think SSI might be behind this?
No clue yet.
Heh, doubt it. They'd have to be true gonks – or at least gonkily overconfident.
entries.maleVariant: Doubt it. They'd have to be true gonks – or at least gonkily overconfident.

entries.femaleVariant: That, or someone hiding behind SSI. Anyone come to mind readily?
entries.maleVariant: Well, that or someone hiding behind SSI. Anyone come to mind readily?

entries.femaleVariant: No clue yet. Anyone besides SSI come to mind readily?
Anything else you wanna tell me... or think maybe you should?
entries.maleVariant: Anything else you wanna tell me, or... think you maybe should?

entries.femaleVariant: Hm... Nope, that about covered it. Liz?
It seems like everything. It's unlikely we'll learn anything, anyway…
So? You've got all you need for now...?
Honey, please. I'm sure V'll turn something up.
Why me of all people? Wouldn't rather have a detective look into it?
entries.maleVariant: Why me of all people? Wouldn't you rather have a detective look into it?

entries.femaleVariant: Prefer to use tried-and-tested contacts.
Generally wise, I guess.
Mayor Rhyne's death – you couldn't quite figure that one out…
I trust you'll be able to crack this one as well.
But I like how you work, I know I can trust you to be thorough.
Weldon Holt? He did kill the last mayor.
And the polls do have him trailing Jeff.
Could be the same people who were behind Mayor Rhyne's murder.
Or Weldon Holt – Jeff's opponent in the race. The polls have him trailing Jeff.
We've had a break-in. Not the usual kind, though.
I'd like you to find him, find out what he wanted.
Anyone else come to mind?
But, it could be anyone, really…
Jeff has many enemies, a lot of them powerful. Heh, we could sit here naming names all day.
I see.
That's why I called you, V. I need you to find out what the hell's going on.
Why'd you hire such a small security firm?
SSI's pretty small-time. Why didn't you go with Arasaka or Militech?
It's what was recommended to us.
On the bright side, we're not dependent on any megacorporations.
Why call me?
Why call me?
Why me?
[Stand]
